# Phase 7: Modpack Import UI Implementation Plan

## Goal
Enable users to import `.mrpack` (Modrinth Modpack) files directly from the UI, with visual feedback.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> I will add a simple "Import" button to the Resources page header for now. In the future, this could be moved to a dedicated "Instance Manager" view if we add one.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Logic
#### [MODIFY] [ModpackService.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModpackService.cs)
- Update [ImportMrPackAsync](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Services/Ecosystem/ModpackService.cs#20-119) to accept `IProgress<string>` (for status text) and `IProgress<double>` (for percentage).
- Implement progress reporting during extraction and file downloading.

### UI / ViewModel
#### [MODIFY] [ResourcesViewModel.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/ViewModels/ResourcesViewModel.cs)
- Add `ImportModpackCommand`.
- Use `OpenFileDialog` to select `.mrpack` files.
- Manage `IsBrowsing` / `IsImporting` states to show/hide loading UI.

#### [MODIFY] [ResourcesPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/ResourcesPage.xaml)
- Add an "Import" button next to the search bar.
- Add a **Progress Overlay** (iOS-style blur or pill) to show import progress.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
1.  Download a sample `.mrpack` from Modrinth (e.g., Sodium + Iris pack).
2.  Click "Import" on Resources page.
3.  Select the file.
4.  Verify the progress overlay appears and updates.
5.  Verify the game version is created in `.minecraft/versions/{pack_name}`.
6.  Verify `mods` are downloaded.
